Installation of LabelImg using PyQt5
-----------------------
LabelImg is a graphical image annotation tool written in Python and using PyQt5. 
The steps I provided indicate the installation and usage of the tool on a Linux system with Python 3.
----------------------

Step 1:
open terminal and run the following commands,
1) sudo apt-get update
2) sudo apt-get install python3
3) sudo apt-get install python3-pip
4) sudo pip3 install pyqt5 lxml

Step 2:
Install the Zip file and extract
1) You can download it from the official repository on GitHub: https://github.com/tzutalin/labelImg
   Click the green "Code" button and select "Download ZIP."
2) Extract the downloaded ZIP file
   Navigate to the directory where you downloaded the ZIP file, and extract its contents.
3) Open a terminal and navigate to the directory where you extracted the labelImg files.
############
for example: $ cd '/home/shiva/labelImg-master' 
############

step 3:
After navigating,
1) run the command: make qt5py3
2) run the command: python3 labelImg.py
so that, This will open LabelImg window

--------------------
